## Facility Identity

- **Name:** Example Research Facility (ERF)
- **Type:** Multi-purpose scientific user facility
- **Mission:** The Example Research Facility is a fictional facility included
  with OSPREY as a starting template. It demonstrates how facility context
  is provided to agents. Replace this entire file with your real facility
  description so agents understand where they are and what they control.

## Systems & Subsystems

The Example Research Facility has three primary systems:

- **Primary Source (PS)** — Main particle/photon source system. Includes
  power supplies, vacuum, RF, and diagnostics subsystems.
- **Transport & Delivery (TD)** — Beam transport, switching, and delivery
  to experimental stations. Includes magnets, steering, and interlock systems.
- **Experimental Stations (ES)** — Six end-stations where users conduct
  experiments. Each station has independent motion control, detectors,
  and sample environments.

Supporting infrastructure:

- **Vacuum System (VAC)** — Ultra-high vacuum across all beamline sections
- **Timing System (TIM)** — Facility-wide synchronization and triggering
- **Personnel Safety System (PSS)** — Access control and radiation interlocks

## Terminology & Naming Conventions

Common terms at the Example Research Facility:

| User says | Means | Channel pattern |
|-----------|-------|-----------------|
| "source current" | Primary source beam current | `PS:DCCT:Current` |
| "vacuum" | Section vacuum pressure | `{SYS}:VAC:{Section}:Pressure` |
| "station status" | Experimental station readiness | `ES{N}:Status` |
| "interlock" | Personnel safety interlock state | `PSS:{Area}:Interlock` |
| "move motor" | Experimental station motor position | `ES{N}:MOT:{Axis}:Position` |

Channel naming follows the pattern: `System:Subsystem:Parameter`

## Operational Context

- The facility operates on a **weekday schedule** (Monday–Friday, 08:00–00:00)
  with maintenance periods on weekends.
- Operators work in **three shifts**: owl (00:00–08:00), day (08:00–16:00),
  and night (16:00–00:00).
- Experimental stations are independently scheduled; some may be active while
  others are in setup or maintenance.
- **Machine studies** are scheduled periodically for accelerator development
  and typically involve non-standard operating conditions.
- The control system uses **EPICS** (Experimental Physics and Industrial
  Control System) as its primary channel access protocol.

